column2: * If you can´t source a logarithmic potentiometer (A) for INPUT you can use a linear pot (B) instead and solder RL1 and RL2 in order to create a fake logarithmic response. If you have a log pot please omit RL1 and RL2.
* Set GAIN_L and GAIN_R for each side of the stereo signal to taste.
* If you want to lower the frequency range being affected by the mid band, increase the value of C8 and C16 (i.g. to 100nF to lower the range from 500Hz/2.2kHz to 100hz/900Hz)
